{
  "text": "A well-known and efficient mechanism of mercury resistance among Gram-positive and Gram-negative microorganisms (including S. meliloti) [CITATION_1] involves mercury reduction encoded by the microbial mer operon located on mobile genetic elements [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "37015333",
